[
  {
    "key": "KAN-5",
    "fields": {
      "summary": "Build PR Refinement agent (counter-voice to PR Review)",
      "description": {
        "content": [
          {
            "content": [
              {
                "text": "Goal",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "type": "hardBreak"
              },
              {
                "text": "Daily pass that reads inline comments left by agents/pr-review and pushes back where the reviewer is wrong, over-eager, or low-signal. Acts as a deliberate adversarial counter-voice (docs/agentic-workflow.md section Design choices).",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "content": [
              {
                "text": "Deliverables",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "type": "hardBreak"
              },
              {
                "text": "* agents/pr-refinement/prompt.md",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "type": "hardBreak"
              },
              {
                "text": "* agents/pr-refinement/README.md",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "type": "hardBreak"
              },
              {
                "text": "* .github/workflows/pr-refinement.yml - daily cron sweep. Note: pr-review (.github/workflows/pr-review.yml) is event-triggered on pull_request events, NOT cron-scheduled. Refinement runs its own daily cron and sweeps all open PRs that already have pr-review inline comments.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "content": [
              {
                "text": "Model choice",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "type": "hardBreak"
              },
              {
                "text": "The doc names CODEX as the counter-model. Implement either a different Claude model via claude_args: --model ..., OR a different action/runtime if going non-Claude. Document the choice.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "content": [
              {
                "text": "Stop condition",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "type": "hardBreak"
              },
              {
                "text": "Cap the refinement so it cannot run forever on the same PR. Options: max N rounds per PR (counter stored in a PR label or hidden HTML comment), or freeze once a human posts on the PR. Pick one and document.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "content": [
              {
                "text": "Acceptance criteria",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "type": "hardBreak"
              },
              {
                "text": "* A PR with pr-review inline comments gets a refinement pass that selectively pushes back.",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "type": "hardBreak"
              },
              {
                "text": "* The cap is exercised: a PR at the limit no longer triggers further refinement.",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "type": "hardBreak"
              },
              {
                "text": "* Run log committed under .github/agent-logs/pr-refinement/pr-PR_NUMBER/RUN_ID.json (matching the pr-review convention at .github/workflows/pr-review.yml:57).",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
